@Comment:	Time is 0:11
@Comment:	Chi can't read the <list of words> as she calls it , but she can read a little and she tries to read the beginning of some pages; although Mot probably wishes Chi were telling the story from the pictures , she cooperates by enunciating carefully as she reads words Chi can't get , and by suggesting that Chi sound words out. Mot also gives semantic clues that are not related to the words on the page , and points to pictures and asks Chi to label them. By the fruit pages , Chi has stopped reading words and tells the story from the pictures.
